<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>hiroto's things (Posts about data-eng)</title><link>https://rodigu.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://rodigu.github.io/categories/cat_data-eng.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents © 2026 &lt;a href="mailto:rmoraisu@proton.me"&gt;rodigu&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Sat, 14 Feb 2026 15:59:21 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>doing the lord's work with python and the walrus operator</title><link>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/airflow-walrus/</link><dc:creator>rodigu</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(actual prod code for airflow)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class="n"&gt;a_data&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;get_users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;partial&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="n"&gt;connection_meta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;connection_meta&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;expand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;code&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;code_a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="p"&gt;),&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class="n"&gt;b_data&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;get_users&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;partial&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="n"&gt;connection_meta&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;connection_meta&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;expand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;code&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;code_b&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="p"&gt;),&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;fetch_content&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;:=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;content_fetch&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a_data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;b_data&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>airflow</category><category>python</category><category>snippet</category><guid>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/airflow-walrus/</guid><pubDate>Sat, 14 Feb 2026 14:54:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>is tsql's `between` inclusive?</title><link>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/tsql-between/</link><dc:creator>rodigu</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;microsoft's &lt;a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/language-elements/between-transact-sql?view=sql-server-ver17" target="_blank"&gt;documentation for between&lt;/a&gt; doesn't mention inclusivity &lt;em&gt;at all&lt;/em&gt; until &lt;a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/language-elements/between-transact-sql?view=sql-server-ver17#b-use--and--instead-of-between" target="_blank"&gt;section b&lt;/a&gt;, which suggests that &lt;code&gt;between&lt;/code&gt; is inclusive. the information is only really &lt;em&gt;explicitly&lt;/em&gt; stated all the way down in &lt;a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/language-elements/between-transact-sql?view=sql-server-ver17#d-use-between-with-datetime-values" target="_blank"&gt;section d&lt;/a&gt;, where it states that (for datetime values, at least), &lt;code&gt;between&lt;/code&gt; is inclusive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;however, as i have come to find out (not before a whole hour of debugging): it ... depends?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/tsql-between/"&gt;Read more…&lt;/a&gt; (2 min remaining to read)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>databases</category><category>sql</category><guid>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/tsql-between/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 16 Dec 2025 20:10:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title>what to do when an airflow task inside a task group fails</title><link>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/airflow-task_group-failure/</link><dc:creator>rodigu</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;checking if a task has failed on airflow is simple enough, and may be done with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code literal-block"&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;from&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nn"&gt;airflow.operators.python&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="kn"&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;get_current_context&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="nd"&gt;@task&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;check_task_failed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;task_id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;bool&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="n"&gt;context&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;get_current_context&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;span class="n"&gt;context&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;"dag_run"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_task_instance&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;task_id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;task_id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;state&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;State&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;FAILED&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/airflow-task_group-failure/"&gt;Read more…&lt;/a&gt; (1 min remaining to read)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>airflow</category><category>python</category><guid>https://rodigu.github.io/posts/data-eng/airflow-task_group-failure/</guid><pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 19:20:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>